> Let's be careful out there.
While we are talking about standards:  let's not forget the respective
ISO and ECMA standards.  Especially the ECMA standards come in handy,
because ECMA makes them available for free on their website.
I once started to make the linux console vt-emulation ECMA-compliant,
but i got side-tracked later on.
